Available now for lease, is approx 102sqm of retail space located on busy Lonsdale Street Braddon.
Located minutes from the CBD this tenancy consists of shop-front and storage and is due for renovation and repaint early 2010.
1 car park is included with the tenancy at an additional charge and amenities are provided to share with other tenants that occupy the building.
The tenancy has a sink unit within and would ideally suit a hairdresser or beautician.

For further information contact CB Richard Ellis Canberra

Grab your slice of Braddon and the Northbourne Avenue Corridor with this substantial 6,270sqm* super site!

- High profile multi-use development site
- 3 combined blocks boasting 3 street frontages
- Existing 6 storey office building with basement
- Permitted uses include hotel, child care, commercial and multi-unit residential
- Short walk to Braddon, CBD and ANU
- Proposed Capital Metro stop directly adjacent
- Sweeping views of surrounding mountain ranges
- NABERS Energy Rating: 0 Stars

The property is being offered for sale by Expression of Interest closing 4pm, Thursday 5th May 2016

The Gallery is a brand new mixed use development located within the sought after precinct of Braddon. 
Braddon has become one of Canberra's most exclusive addresses when it comes to trend setting, location, fashion, dining & retail. The Gallery is no exception adding a premium offering to Mort Street. With most of the residential and commercial units locked away, there is only two remaining retail opportunity available.

Available for lease is a retail unit being 70sqm* in size. The unit benefits from excellent street exposure, high ceilings, large glass shopfront and would suite a range of users. Public parking is situated along Mort Street. 

With future developments planned which will only increase the popularity of the area, this is a fantastic opportunity to lease a ground floor retail suite this size in Braddon which are not readily available. 


For further information or to arrange an inspection please contact CBRE

*Approx.
